name: OCKAnyContact
desc: A protocol that allows you to query and display a custom contact data type.

items.name: var title: String?
items.desc: A string that represents this contact to the patient.

items.name: var organization: String?
items.desc: The organization to which the contact belongs.

items.name: var role: String?
items.desc: A description of this contact’s role.

items.name: var category: OCKContactCategory?
items.desc: The relationship between the patient and the contact.

items.name: var phoneNumbers: [OCKLabeledValue]?
items.desc: An array of the contact’s phone numbers.

items.name: var messagingNumbers: [OCKLabeledValue]?
items.desc: An array of numbers at which the contact can be messaged.

items.name: var emailAddresses: [OCKLabeledValue]?
items.desc: An array of the contact’s email addresses.

items.name: var otherContactInfo: [OCKLabeledValue]?
items.desc: An array of other information which the patient can use to reach the contact.

items.name: var asset: String?
items.desc: Specifies the location of some asset associated with this object.

items.name: var groupIdentifier: String?
items.desc: A user-defined group identifier you can use to query and sort results.

items.name: var id: String
items.desc: A human-readable unique identifier that is never shown to a user.

items.name: var notes: [OCKNote]?
items.desc: An array of notes associated with the contact object.

items.name: var remoteID: String?
items.desc: A string value that represents a unique identifier, which a remote database uses optionally.

items.name: func belongs(to: OCKAnyCarePlan) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether a contact belongs to a specific care plan.
